                         dam-model-statistical-analysis

read data from a file using the disk access model and perform statistical
analysis on them.

each line in the input file consists of five numbers separated by a space:  the
x, y, z coordinates, the intensity (i), and the time (t).

usage:

  dam.apl [option] [args]

options:

  sort data in a file and store it in a directory:

    s [input_file] [output_dir]

  analyze the sorted data and output some of its descriptive statistics:

    a [input_dir] [memory_buffer_size] [block_size] [min_x] [max_x] [min_y] [max_y] [basket_size] [z|i|t]
